EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Communication from the Mayor  -  "AN ACT relating to providing accidental and special accidental death benefits, a line-of-duty award and health insurance coverage to eligible survivors of a certain member of the uniformed force of the New York city fire department who was killed in action while serving in Iraq as a member of the Army National Guard." A.11892 / S.7797
EventItemMatterName: Providing accidental and special accidental death benefits (S.7797/A.11892)

EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Communication for the Mayor - Mayor's veto and disapproval message of Introductory Number 124-A, in relation to the requirements of the campaign finance program for city elections, the requirements of transition and inauguration entities for candidates elected to the offices of mayor, public advocate, comptroller, borough president, and member of the city council, participation in the New York City Campaign Finance Program by self-funded candidates, the debate program, and limiting the use of government resources during an election year.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor's Veto of Int. No. 124-A, Requirements of the campaign finance program for city elections.

EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Communication for the Mayor - Mayor's veto and disapproval message of Introductory Number 371-A, in relation to application of contribution limits of the New York City Campaign Finance Program to all candidates for the offices of mayor, public advocate, comptroller, borough president, and member of the city council, and prohibiting candidates from accepting contributions, loans or security for such loans from corporations.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor's Veto of Int. No. 371-A, Selected requirements of the NYC Campaign Finance Program.

EventItemActionText: This Mayor's Message was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Communication for the Mayor - Mayor's veto and disapproval message of Introductory Number 466-A, in relation to application of the public disclosure requirements of the New York City Campaign Finance Program to all candidates for the offices of mayor, public advocate, comptroller, borough president, and member of the city council.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor's Veto of Int. No. 466-A, Application of selected requirements of the NYC Campaign Finance Program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the federal government to only purchase military uniforms made wholly in the United States, and to give New York City its fair share of military uniform purchasing contracts.
EventItemMatterName: Federal government to only purchase military uniforms made wholly in the US.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming a street David Michael Ruddle Street, in the Borough of the Bronx.
EventItemMatterName: Name Change, David Michael Ruddle Street, Bronx

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the U.S. Congress and President Bush to immediately adopt all the recommendations of the 9/11 Commission that affect the allocation of homeland security funding to New York City and address problems with the city’s emergency command and communication protocol.
EventItemMatterName: Immediately adopt all the recommendations of the 9/11 Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution commending the Campaign for Fiscal Equity, the law firm of Simpson, Thatcher & Bartlett and all those who have worked with them for their continuing advocacy for the children of the City of New York, and calling upon the Governor and the State Legislature to fully and fairly provide the means to insure that all New York City school children immediately receive a sound basic education.
EventItemMatterName: Commending the Campaign for Fiscal Equity

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon New York State Governor George Pataki to grant executive clemency to Ms. Sharon Richardson, who, during her 14 years of incarceration, has participated in countless rehabilitating programs, humanitarian activities and educational initiatives, thus proving herself to be deserving of clemency.
EventItemMatterName: Grant executive clemency to Ms. Sharon Richardson.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to vest the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene with authority to inspect and enforce regulations governing the operations of slaughterhouses in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Dep't of Health and Mental Hygiene with authority to inspect and enforce regulations governing the operations of slaughterhouses.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of Assembly bill A.02835, sponsored by Assemblyman Richard Gottfried, to amend the New York State Urban Development Corporation Act in relation to subjecting various actions the Urban Development Corporation is authorized to take respecting real property to the provisions of Section 197-c of the New York City Charter and calling upon the New York State Legislature to enact this legislation.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the NYS Urban Development Corporation Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution pursuant to Section 19-511.1 of the Administrative Code of the City of New York to review one hundred thirteen determinations by the Taxi and Limousine Commission to approve applications for the renewal of a license to operate a base station.
EventItemMatterName: Base Station License Review

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring callers to the 311 system to identify themselves by name and address if the nature of their complaint requires the dispatch of the Police Department, Fire Department or EMS, and making it a crime if such call is a false report.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring callers to the 311 system to identify themselves by name and address.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the responsibility of an owner, lessee, tenant or person in charge of a vacant lot to maintain such lot and adjacent areas.
EventItemMatterName: Responsibility of an owner, lessee, tenant or person in charge of a vacant lot to maintain such lot and adjacent areas.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing signage requiring lower speeds and other pedestrian-friendly actions when operators of any form of transportation are within one block of a naturally occurring retirement community or one block of a senior citizens center.
EventItemMatterName: Providing signage requiring lower speeds and other pedestrian-friendly actions around retirement community or senior citizens center.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the regulation and licensing of residential contractors.
EventItemMatterName: Regulation and licensing of residential contractors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to auditing and implementing diversity and eradicating discrimination in all City operations.
EventItemMatterName: Auditing and implementing diversity and eradicating discrimination in all City operations.
